    {
      "id": "a4777d99-25c3-4dd5-89e7-2e2ce06ad072",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "- int is a primitive data type. It is raw, naked data.\r\n- Integer (with a capital I) is a Wrapper Class. It is a full-blown Object that acts like a box. Inside that box, it holds a primitive int.\r\n- When you define a class like class Node1<T>, Java has a strict rule: The Generic type <T> can ONLY be an Object. It cannot be a primitive.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "a4777d99-25c3-4dd5-89e7-2e2ce06ad072"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "4da1ae42-bd46-41f1-bf79-0eb953b22cab",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "           D\r\n        /     \\\r\n       B       F \r\n      / \\     /  \\\r\n    A    C   E    G",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "4da1ae42-bd46-41f1-bf79-0eb953b22cab"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "0bc2e5d2-6dc7-434f-9d1a-9f8540a96700",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "1. Tree traversals  \r\n- Depth-first search (DFS)  \r\n    + Preorder: visit, left, right  \r\n        eg. D (BAC) (FEG)\r\n    + Inorder: left, visit, right  \r\n        eg. (ABC) D (EFG)\r\n    + Postorder: left, right, visit  \r\n        eg. (ACB) (EGF) D\r\n\r\n- Breadth-first search (BFS)  \r\n    eg. D (BF) (ACEG)\r\n\r\n2. Depth of a node  \r\n=length or distance from the root\r\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "0bc2e5d2-6dc7-434f-9d1a-9f8540a96700"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e03b7367-c864-4b2d-83f3-6f3c6a258ab8",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Exercise 2: Print the tree using the preorder (i.e. visit, left, right)\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "e03b7367-c864-4b2d-83f3-6f3c6a258ab8"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "3b28702e-89f4-4955-b37b-cb307a84f21c",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "public <T> void pre_order_print(BinaryTreeNode<T> root){\r\n    if(root==null){\r\n        return;\r\n    }\r\n    else{\r\n        IO.print(root.data.toString() + \" \");\r\n        pre_order_print(root.left);\r\n        pre_order_print(root.right);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\npre_order_print(root2);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "3b28702e-89f4-4955-b37b-cb307a84f21c",
        "executionSummary": {
